    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6a6037e5_d8ab04da",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/host/libs/libOpenglRender/SyncThread.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-20T00:31:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "does it set the object state to something that can be detected from the caller? constructors don\u0027t return values, so there has to be a way to detect a failure",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 72,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 72,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "50750c51030f2028587e14d95ab977f4fb125093",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6a6037e5_26ac3a9b",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/host/libs/libOpenglRender/SyncThread.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-20T19:17:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "good question. The users of this class pretty much only interact without expecting return values, but if we do attempt to create a sync thread and communicate with it without a parent context, that\u0027s near-instant deadlock due to fences on the guest not being signaled. A fallback path that signals anyway sounded appealing at first, but a) adds a branch to performance critical paths and b) as no other code will use the constructor explicitly, it means we must have ended up running getSyncThread in an improper usage.\n\nSo, emugl_crash_reporter it is.",
      "parentUuid": "6a6037e5_d8ab04da",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 72,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 72,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "50750c51030f2028587e14d95ab977f4fb125093",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
